Used to like this restaurant a lot. Relatively quiet. Great food. Plenty of choice. But recently getting set back. Service not so nice as before. Dishes quality drops to average Chinese restaurant level

Originally founded as a seafood restaurant, the place nowadays is famous for dim sum and certain specialities such as roast pig where they roast the whole piglet in an open fire place outside the shop for you to see. Nice nearby view of a lake and a distant temple. There's a bus stop right outside the restaurant, and the place is reachable by minibus too. Parking space are limited at the place and always requires waiting on weekends.

reviews.text: 服務態度不錯，食物保持水準，價錢比起沙田酒店中茶便宜，物有所值，鄰近海邊，風景不錯，有免費車位。
点心不錯，魚湯海鮮米粉 推薦。價格中等，食品水平好。
食物一般段, 酒店級價錢, 貴...
好正，點心好食，環境清幽，坐戶外可以一邊食一邊望住海境，最重要是可以同心愛狗狗一齊，飲完茶可由斜路行落附近小形碼頭遠望對面觀音佛像，有船家載人到附近釣魚
食品幾好，價錢稍貴，乳豬相當好食，但交通極不方便。

a wonderful and uncontaminated village to visit if you love Hong Kong old history and culture :) remember to try the traditional cakes! (but it is a pity that the schedule of ferry doesn't match with the time of salt pan tour.)

It is a very peaceful place with very few visitors. It is said to a tourists spot in HK but there is hardly anything very attractive about the place. The high point is the boat ride which takes to the off shore Island. The place is historical sites which gives an idea about lifestyle  in the olden days. There are olden houses at short distances but none you can walk in. If you have limited time in hand as a tourist, you can skip this place.

Buy ferry tickets at any one of the booths next to the Saikung public piers and depart from No.10. It's HK$50 for a return ticket. Make sure you check the ferry times as the last one depends on the tide. 

This small island features a chapel, a salt farm, a few derelict houses and a small indoor exhibition of ancient artefacts dug up over the years. 

The chapel has been preserved and is a sight to see but note there's a request for appropriate clothes to be worn if going inside. 

A couple of stalls and a restaurant are nearby the pier and a easy trail around and over the island. There's a causeway to the nearby Kau Sai Chau public golf course.

Interesting historical site. It is a small island but lots of informative signage as it is now a revived heritage  site. There is a small snack stall near the jetty so bring cash to try some local rice cakes. We paddled over in canoes from Sai Kung.
今天暢遊了一天，有旅遊、美食、體驗，十分充實

環境一流
鹽田仔，正名鹽田梓。梓代指故鄉，存思鄉意。鹽田梓村，始自18世紀客家人遷入，曬鹽為生；19世紀中天主教傳入，後全村奉信天主教；20世紀90年代，村荒廢。21世紀保育復修。聖若瑟小堂及鹽田復修項目分別獲文化遺産保護奬。小島大不大，景點集中。環島一週約1小時。島上間蕩，可浮生半日。
